1) Pet lvl/atk/dmg output<br>
IMHO Arch Mage ... Master of the Elements ... strongest Pet class *LOOOOOOOOOOL* should fit in theyr title ... i mean who wants a mage in a exp group in high lvls ? no one ... why ? he does no DMG ... our main dmg source was the PET ... you nerved our only real dmg source away (since my god damn shock of fiery swords even gets resisted from the lvl 7 fisher girl in freeport!!!) you thought magicians are overpower and nerved our pets .. what you didnt think of is .. that our pet is the only possible way to kill a mob ... with lvl 60 i have a hard time to solo some lvl 48+ mobs... in PVP i have NO chance against any melee (even if i use earth pet) since the roots/stuns or other spells from my pets are ALWAYS ressisted... we dont have anything like root/snare so we have to be able to relie on our pets. lets take OS .. i fight a froglok shaman lvl 45 ... i have to chainnuke like a madman to get him down before my 57 earth pet runs out of HPs ... its not even possible to try it with fire/air/water couse the pets will either die or the mob comes after you since you have to chainnuke and you AND your pet dies. anyway.. why are beastlord pets stronger then mage pets ?? beastlord can slow, heal, tank, and theyr pet is stronger then ours.. wow .. lets see .. i can .. mmm .. nuke ? well i think i have pretty decent AC for a mage with 856AC so i can at least tank some hits ... but still. so all in all i agree .. pets should be the casters lvl or neg1 or 2 lvls so they are useful for us ... im in a high end guild and i use my pet ZERO times .. if i cast a pet its dead in 2 seconds anyway so its a waste of mana. solo exp ? no chance... i 2box me and a 60 cleric and CH my pet every few seconds (earth pet) couse its HP drop so fast (even with aego on it) that its hardly worth to solo since i will use all my mana on 1 mob couse of either chaincasting nukes or pet heals.<br>
